<font color="#FF0000">WANTABE</font><br>
<tt>Thu Apr 17  3:01:45 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
In january of 1987 i was in a combat veterans rap group at<br>
our local Vet center. At that time the movie &quot;Platoon&quot; was<br>
released and a newspaper reporter took the group to see the<br>
film. After the screening the reporter got his scoop,by <br>
interviewing us at a local ginmill. The drinks were on the <br>
paper. A staff photograher took our picture. The photo and<br>
story appeared in the next morning edition. <br>
   Up until then, I kept Nam out of the workplace, but with<br>
my mug on the front page of the local rag, oh boy... so this<br>
reserve type, a real weekend warrior gung ho, high and tight, <br>
spit shined shoes co worker approaches me in the elevator.<br>
&quot;I envy you,&quot; he sez to me<br>
&quot;What are you talking about,&quot; I reply<br>
&quot;you tasted it&quot;<br>
&quot;tasted what?&quot;<br>
&quot;Combat!&quot; He goes.<br>
&quot;Yeah, sure your right,well ya didn't miss a thing asshole<br>
so if you will excuse me I got a life to live.&quot;<br>
Just another Wantabe!!<br>
   Couple years later the War against Sadam is happening.<br>
I come to the job one morning and old Oorah I play soldier<br>
once a month and every two weeks during the summer ain't at<br>
his desk.<br>
&quot;Oh,&quot; I sez, &quot;where is desk number 23 this fine Monday <br>
morning.&quot;<br>
Old Nosey Rosie the company know it all pipes up<br>
&quot;His reserve unit got called up and he is on his way to the <br>
Gulf War.&quot;<br>
Dumb ass. Maybe he will get his wish.<br>
Yep it looks like he a Gonabee.<br><br>

